text:
I started my first dev job as a full stack dev and feeling incredibly overwhelmed is this normal? | The code base uses OOP where i've mostly used functional paradigm and I've also only used firebase and a small amount of express and postgres for my back end up until now. I'm not working with postgresql and restify for my backend and typeORM for the schemas.

&#x200B;

My problem is the codebase seems so large like one million lines and it's a monolith. Theres also so much inheritance going on it's insane. I feel like i'm beginning to understand sections but other days I feel absolutely lost. I feel like i'm in over my head, but my boss has been reassuring tbf and seems comitted to helping me get there, but i'm beginning to question if I'm even smart enough to do this.

&#x200B;

I'm basically the only guy working on this web app with my boss whos the technical director, am I just dumb or is it usually like this? I've been here two weeks so far.
